# Dashboard login accounts — copy to `.Users` on the server and edit.
# One block per person. Lines may be indented; a trailing | on each field is optional.
#
# Section headers: use `# Name` or a three-line `//` block, e.g.
#   //||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
#   //              3806                //
#   //||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
#
# access: * or all = Admin (all stores). Otherwise comma-separated store numbers = Store level.
# Admin accounts can ONLY be created by editing this file — not via the dashboard UI.
# Named admins: NicholasAntonello, ThomasRead, AshOwens
#
# Usernames are case-insensitive at login. Passwords are case-sensitive.
# Passwords: use temporary plaintext for first sign-in only — users are prompted to
# set a new password on first login; the new password is saved encrypted (scrypt:…).
# Or pre-hash with scripts/hash-dashboard-password.js if you do not want the first-login prompt.
#
# Password rules after first login:
#   Admin (* access): 8+ chars, must include capital letter, special character, AND number.
#   Store accounts:   8+ chars, must include at least ONE of capital, special, or number.
# Optional CB username (e.g. CB3811): same password and welcome name, opens the dashboard
# with blue/yellow/red colours instead of green/yellow/red (colour-blind friendly).
#
# Store logins see two sign-in buttons: "Login to dashboard" and "Login as MIC".
# Admin logins see a single Sign in button.

# Admin — Nicholas Antonello
NicholasAntonello |
CBNicholasAntonello |
changeme-admin-password |
*

# Admin — Thomas Read
ThomasRead |
CBThomasRead |
changeme-admin-password |
*

# Admin — Ash Owens
AshOwens |
CBAshOwens |
changeme-admin-password |
*

//||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
//              3811                //
//||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
3811 |
CB3811 |
changeme-3811-password |
3811

//||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
//              3806                //
//||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||//
3806 |
CB3806 |
changeme-3806-password |
3806

